# My Project Ecosystem

This file loads into every Claude Code conversation automatically.
Use it to map your projects so Claude understands cross-project relationships.

## Project Map

| Project | Path | What It Is |
|---------|------|------------|
| My App | `~/projects/my-app/` | Main web application (React + Node.js) |
| API Server | `~/projects/api-server/` | Backend API service |
| Shared Libs | `~/projects/shared-libs/` | Common utilities shared across projects |
| Infrastructure | `~/projects/infra/` | Terraform + CI/CD configuration |
| Claude System | `~/claude-system/` | This meta-system: skills, agents, rules, knowledge base |

## Key Relationships

1. **My App depends on API Server** — Frontend calls the API; changes to API endpoints may require frontend updates
2. **Shared Libs is used by both** — Breaking changes in shared-libs affect both my-app and api-server
3. **Infrastructure deploys everything** — CI/CD pipelines, staging, production

## Working Conventions

- Feature branches off `main`, PRs required for merge
- Tests must pass before merging
- Use conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, refactor:, test:)

## Skills Reference

Available slash-commands (from `~/.claude/skills/`):
- `/carryover` — Generate session recovery document before compaction
- `/debate` — Multi-agent adversarial analysis of hard decisions
- `/plan-deep` — Recursive hierarchical planning for complex tasks
- `/gh-scout` — Discover and vet GitHub repos for patterns
- `/research-papers` — Search academic papers across databases
- `/research-books` — Find and read books from open sources
- `/visualize` — Create 2D diagrams (D2, Mermaid, Markmap)
- `/digest` — Process large data exports into organized archives
- `/context-audit` — Measure context window efficiency
- `/session-log` — Archive session to project directory
- `/session-id` — Find current or past session IDs
- `/migrate` — Create context migration prompt for new conversation
